ode class=\"language-text\">validationRules</code> property, its child property <code class=\"language-text\">key</code> must be same as <code class=\"language-text\">name</code> property, otherwise validation not performed. Submitting data to the server or calling the <code class=\"language-text\">validate</code> method validation executed.</p>\n<p>In the following sample, first editor value submitted without select any date, so the default error message will be displayed below the <code class=\"language-text\">DatePicker</code> element. Second editor configured with the <code class=\"language-text\">validating</code> event with the handler. In handler event <code class=\"language-text\">errorMessage</code> argument value modified and it will show below the <code class=\"language-text\">DatePicker</code> element.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"csharp\"><pre class=\"language-csharp\"><code class=\"language-csharp\">@<span class=\"token keyword\">using</span> Syncfusion<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>EJ2<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>RazorComponents\n@<span class=\"token keyword\">using</span> Syncfusion<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>EJ2<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>RazorComponents<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>InPlaceEditor\n\n<span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>div <span class=\"token keyword\">class</span><span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"control-section inplace-control-section\"</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n    <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>table <span class=\"token keyword\">class</span><span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"table-section\"</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n        <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>tr<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n            <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>td <span class=\"token keyword\">class</span><span clas